nodes.bodyText:
When this class first runs, you won't know the right value of inForeground for sure. Did this code start executing when the initial state was in foreground? Or in background?
So, I propose that you change this from a boolean to an enum, that looks like:
enum ForegroundState {
    FOREGROUND,
    BACKGROUND,
    UNKNOWN;
}

The class constructor would initialize a member like:
ApplicationForegroundTracker() {
    this.state = ForgroundState.UNKNOWN;
}

Or perhaps:
ApplicationForegroundTracker() {
    this.state = determineForegroundState();
}

where determineForegroundState() is something like this:
https://stackoverflow.com/a/40804658/695787 perhaps

